    "body": "## Goal\n\nAdd a curated Verdikta class whose arbiters use Venice.ai privacy-focused text inference with a clearly defined minimum privacy guarantee.\n\n## Context\n\nVenice exposes an OpenAI-compatible API and identifies model privacy characteristics. The approved default is to curate only models classified Private, TEE, or E2EE; models that are merely Anonymized are excluded. Arbiter operators provide their own Venice API keys.\n\nThis initiative spans the shared class map in `verdikta-common` and the provider, configuration, health, installer, test, and operator surfaces in `verdikta-arbiter`.\n\nReferences:\n\n- https://docs.venice.ai/api-reference/api-spec\n- https://docs.venice.ai/models/overview\n- https://venice.ai/privacy\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] The next available curated ClassID is assigned and documented.\n- [ ] The class definition admits only approved Venice text models meeting the minimum privacy classification.\n- [ ] Arbiters can authenticate with operator-supplied Venice API keys and execute evaluation requests.\n- [ ] Provider failures, unsupported privacy modes, unavailable models, and invalid configuration fail safely and observably.\n- [ ] Installer, health checks, tests, and operator documentation cover the new class.\n\n## Validation\n\nRegister an arbiter for the curated class in staging and complete an end-to-end evaluation using an approved Venice model. Demonstrate rejection of an unapproved Anonymized model and capture provider, model, privacy classification, and version evidence.\n\n## Scope\n\nIn scope:\n\n- Venice text inference\n- Private, TEE, and E2EE model classifications\n- Shared ClassID metadata and arbiter integration\n- Operator-supplied credentials\n\nOut of scope:\n\n- Venice models classified only as Anonymized\n- Image, audio, video, and unrelated Venice endpoints\n- General dynamic admission of every model returned by Venice",
